(1, 4, 5, '<h2>How to Travel From NJP to Jaigaon</h2>\r\n<p>Jaigaon is a touristy town of Alipurduar District in the state of West Bengal. It is a small valley located near the low-lying hills of the Himalayan mountains. The city is surrounded by many tea gardens and Torsa river flows at the lower end of the town. &nbsp;The town is situated at the India-Bhutan border with Phuentsholing, therefore you will get a chance to enjoy some Bhutanese places too. The town is quite small and you can easily see the city on foot. As of census 2011, the population of Jaigaon is just 42,254. Therefore if you are planning to Visit Bhutan Jaigaon should be in your must-visit list.</p>\r\n<p>Now, if you are thinking about going there from New Jalpaiguri, you have to know all the possible ways. Well, that is why we are here to help you and give you the exact information about going there from NJP to Jaigaon.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Travel Jaigaon</h2>\r\n<p>Jaigaon has plenty of reasons to attract travelers. As it is located near Bhutan, you can experience the mesmerizing beauty of this country. Bhutan Gate is located near the city. As a result, you will get a chance to know and enjoy this eye-catching Bhutanese architecture. The temperature of the town is quite pleasing. The temperature stays at 22 degrees to 30 degrees during summer and 10 degrees to 24 degrees Celsius during winter. This town becomes a must visit place if you want to escape the intense heat of summer.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Jaigaon by Road</h2>\r\n<p>If you want to travel from NJP to Jaigaon, there are many options available. Bhutan post usually operates bus services from New Jalpaiguri to Jaigaon for 3 times a week. You can even go to Siliguri. From P.C Mittal Bus Stand, buses are available to travel Jaigaon. Buses approximately take 4 hours and 15 minutes to reach there.<br />\r\nJourney time becomes short if you book a taxi. Taxis usually take approximately 2 hours depending on the traffic and road conditions. That is why we always prefer to get a pre-book taxi from NJP. You can pre-book our car just one-day before your scheduled journey and we will pick you up. The process is completely hassle-free and convenient, just give a call to book and we will be there to pick you.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Jaigaon by Train</h2>\r\n<p>There is no railway station in Jaigaon. The nearest railway station is Hasimara and this is why Indian Railway offers train service from NJP to Hasimara only. The journey takes usually 3 hours and 38 minutes. Here, as you can see the journey time is quite long. After arriving Hashimara, you have to take an auto to finally reach Jaigaon. The journey can be full of hassles.</p>\r\n<h2>How to Return From Jaigaon</h2>\r\n<p>Finally, we have guided you to know all the details related to reaching Jaigaon from New Jalpaiguri. And now maybe you are thinking about the process of returning. Please don\'t worry because here at Himalayan Wheels, we always are here to help you out.</p>\r\n<p>During the time of returning, you can take all the above-mentioned mediums to return. But if you want to return your home quite comfortably after enjoying the beauty of Jaigaon, you can always opt for our car rental service.</p>\r\n<h2>Why You Should Choose Us</h2>\r\n<p>Himalayan Wheels is an agency that provides car rental services to the tourists so that they can enjoy the peace and beauty of nature without worrying about the medium of their journey. Here at Himalayan Wheels, our chief focus is your comfort. We always ensure that you reach your desired destinations safely on time and without wasting any extra penny. So why are you waiting? Just call us to book a car to enjoy the mesmerizing beauty of Jaigaon and if you have any queries, please don&#39;t hesitate to contact us.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:00:52', '2019-07-09 04:47:11', NULL),
(2, 4, 7, '<h2>How to Travel FROM NJP to Lava</h2>\r\n<p>There are limited places in West Bengal where you can enjoy the snowfall and lava is one of them. This magnificent village is located 30 kilometers east of the Kalimpong town in the State of West Bengal. Blessed with rich flora and fauna, Lava becomes one of the most recommended tourist destinations. The village is situated at the altitude of 7100ft and as it is located in the dense forest, it is too quiet and romantic. The journey to Lava is quite scenic as it is surrounded by many alpine trees.</p>\r\n<h2>Reasons to visit Lava</h2>\r\n<p>Lava can be tagged as a tourist\'s paradise as it is full of attractive places. You can fall in love with that village once you visit it. Lava\'s Kagyu Thekchen Ling Monastery is a Buddhist Monastery situated in the lap of Himalaya. Visit the monastery to get spiritually connected to Buddhism. ChangeryFall is situated at a distance of 10 km from magnificent Lava. It is quite popular among tourists for its scenic beauty. Neora Valley National Park is another main attraction of Lava. If you want to enjoy the company of none other than nature, you must visit this park. You can even see many animals such as tigers, red panda, leopard and many more. Tiffin Dara View Point is another famous place for enjoying sunrise and sunset. Now if you are planning to travel from NJP to Lava, you have come in the right place.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Lava by Road</h2>\r\n<p>If you are planning to visit Lava by bus, you have to come Siliguri first. Take an auto from NJP and reach P.C Mittal bus stand, from where you can opt for a bus to Lava via Garubathan or Kalimpong. The distance between NJP to Lava is 96 km and buses usually take too much time to reach. Shared Taxis are not available for NJP to Lava. As a result, we always advise you to get a pre-booked taxi from Himalayan Wheels at a cheaper price.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Lava by Train</h2>\r\n<p>There is no rail station at Lava. The nearest rail station is Siliguri Junction which is far away from Lava. As you can see, going to Lava by train is completely troublesome. And this is why you should always opt for a pre-booked taxi from a renowned agency like Himalayan Wheels.</p>\r\n<h2>How to Return from Lava</h2>\r\n<p>After enjoying the beauty of Lava, returning from the village is quite troublesome. You can not return by train as Lava has no railway station. Finding a returning bus is quite difficult too. But don\'t worry, we are here to help you from this trouble. Even while you are returning, you can pre-book our car rental service.</p>\r\n<h2>Why You Should Choose Us</h2>\r\n<p>Himalayan Wheels car rental service is your one-stop solution when all others fail to offer safe and convenient. Himalayan Wheels provides a comprehensive range of new and late model vehicles to suit all of your budgets and size requirements. Whether you need something for enjoying the magnificent towns or touring the open roads, Himalayan Wheels has the right vehicle for all your travel needs. Just give us a call to pre-book or Contact us for any further inquiries.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:01:00', '2019-07-09 05:11:38', NULL),
(3, 4, 8, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Mirik</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Mirik is a small beautiful town located in Darjeeling District of West Bengal. Mirik is a popular tourist destination because of its climate, easy accessibility, and natural environment. The weather of Mirik stays charming all through the years. It never reaches to the point of extreme cold like Darjeeling because Mirik has an average elevation of 1495m. The temperature of the city stays 30-degree Celsius during summer and a minimum of 1 degree Celsius during winter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New Jalpaiguri Railway Station or Njp is the main railway station located near Mirik. Njp serves the city Siliguri which is the largest city of North Bengal. It also serves as the entry point of Sikkim, Bhutan, Nepal, and even the northeastern states. As a result, many long-distance trains pass through that station. If you successfully arrive in NJP, there are several options to choose to reach Mirik such as Taxi, bus or by rail.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>NJP to Mirik by Taxi</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Mirik is well connected with many cities such as Darjeeling, Siliguri, Karseung by Road. Mirik is located near 52 km (32 mi) northwest of Siliguri city and 49 km (30 mi) south-southwest of Darjeeling town. After arriving at New Jalpaiguri, you will get plenty of options to choose to reach Mirik. There are many private taxis available. Sometimes drivers demand more and their demand increases during the high tourist season. There are many Taxi Rental services available too but we are the only one who offers car rental at a cheap and reasonable price. All you have to do is that just pre-book us before one day of your scheduled journey from NJP to Mirik.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>NJP to Mirik by Shared Taxi</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If your plan is to go for a little cheap option, you can take a shared taxi. You can find many shared taxis from Siliguri. But you have to bear troubles if you want to get a shared taxi from Siliguri as you must take an auto to reach there. Shared ta