(5, 4, 6, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Kalimpong</h2>\r\n<p>Have you recently planned to visit Kalimpong? But do you know that Kalimpong is one of the major travel destinations of North Bengal? It is situated at an average elevation of 1250 meters. The town is close to Bhutan-Tibet-Sikkim border on the eastern part of Darjeeling Himalayas. The astonishing and charming weather of Kalimpong attracts tourists to visit the town. Blessed with rich flora and fauna, Kalimpong is the perfect mix of ancient tradition with modern life. Now if your journey starts from NJP to Kalimpong, you have come in the right place as we are going to describe all the transportation options needed to visit Kalimpong.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Kalimpong</h2>\r\n<p>Kalimpong is famous for many scenic places and astonishing architectures. Deolo Hill is the highest point of the town at an elevation of 2000 meters which offers a panoramic view of Kalimpong. A beautiful piece of construction wrapped with a legend of being haunted, Morgan house is an excellent example of colonial architecture in Kalimpong. The mansion was constructed on the 1930s by Mr. and Mrs. Morgan but now it is turned into a tourist lodge by West Bengal Tourism Development Corporation. Founded by Dalai Lama in 1976 Jang Dong Palriffo Brang Gompa is the perfect example of the religious belief of Buddhists. There are many other Buddhist monasteries located in Kalimpong, thus making it one of the major hubs for Buddhism followers. Kalimpong is the major flower producing center in India which produces 80% of flowers and then export to other places. Kalimpong&#39;s Cactus Nursery is quite famous among tourists where you can see different types of cactus along with 400 types of orchids. Kalimpong is favouritefor adventure seekers too, as it offers them to do hiking, river rafting, paragliding and many more. For nature lover to the adventure seeker, there is always something to offer for everyone thus making it an ideal place to visit.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Kalimpong by Road</h2>\r\n<p>Kalimpong is nicely connected with various places including New Jalpaiguri. From NJP, the distance of Kalimpong is about 73kms by road. If you take a bus, it will take approximately 2.5 hours to reach Kalimpong depending on the traffic and road condition. Buses are usually available from Siliguri&rsquo;s Tenzing Norgay Bus Terminal on Hill Cart Road. And the distance between Siliguri to Kalimpong is 65 km. Shared taxi is available from only Siliguri and you have to get an auto from NJP to reach Siliguri. This could be a journey full of hassles. Please remember it that they will not start unless the car is full of passengers and your luggage is going to be on the roof-top of the car.</p>\r\n<p>Pre-booked Taxi is available from NJP to Kalimpong. They usually charge more from the exact price. We at Himalayan Wheels are the only one which offers car rental service at a convenient price.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Kalimpong by Train</h2>\r\n<p>There is no railway station located at Kalimpong. The nearest railway station is Siliguri Junction. As you can see, reaching Kalimpong on the train is impossible. If you want to reach Siliguri from NJP, you can get a train but still, you have to opt for a pre-paid taxi or shared jeeps to reach Kalimpong. The process is quite troublesome thus you recommend you to opt for a pre-booked taxi.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Kalimpong by Air</h2>\r\n<p>There is no airport in Kalimpong either. The nearest airport is Bagdogra which is 75 km away from the town. You can opt for a pre-paid or shared taxis to reach Bagdogra from New Jalpaiguri. We also offer car rental service from Bagdogra to Kalimpong. Just pre-book us and reach your desired location quite comfortably and safely.</p>\r\n<p>As you can see, reaching Kalimpong from NJP is full of hassles. Traveling to Kalimpong by air and even by train is completely impossible. The only option to reach there is by a shared taxi or a pre-booked car. You have to sacrifice your comfort for the sake of money if you choose to travel by shared taxi. The good choice is none other than a pre-paid taxi from us. Just book us and enjoy even the journey to magnificent Kalimpong.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:01:25', '2019-07-09 05:56:40', NULL),
(6, 4, 10, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Kolakham</h2>\r\n<p>Nestled in the lap of the evergreen forest of Eastern Himalaya, Kolakham is a small beautiful hamlet located at an altitude of 6500 ft. The place is ideal for every nature lovers who are finding adventure as well as peace. Blessed with rich flora and fauna, this scenic hamlet is located 8km away from Lava and 38 km from Kalimpong. There are many attractive places, many rare species, animals and trees available in Kolakham. Thus, making it a paradise for every traveler. Now if you want to visit this mesmerizing hamlet by traveling from NJP to Kolakham, you have come in the right place. But let us first introduce you to some of the attractive places of Kolakham first.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Kolakham</h2>\r\n<p>Neora Valley National Park is the prime attraction of Kolakham. Here you can enjoy the picturesque green forest with a variety of birds and some of the very rare creatures. A jungle safari by a jeep and trekking through the forest can bring you a lot of joy. The trips through the deep jungle, full of tropical forest and most rare birds will make this trip a lifetime memory which you can cherish forever.</p>\r\n<p>Changery Falls is a beautiful waterfall located at Kolakham. After the 3 km drive and 1.5 km of walk, you will finally reach to this mesmerizing fall in the deep forest of Himalaya. The sound of the falling water and the chirping of the birds will take your breath away if you are a pure nature lover.</p>\r\n<p>Lava is just 8 km away from Kolakham which is also an attractive place to visit. Enjoy the beauty of the lava monastery and be amazed by seeing this ancient architecture. Take shelter in the lap of nature by walking on the canopy bridge and come closer to the forest full of flora and fauna.</p>\r\n<p>To hide completely from the word, this place is the ideal one. You can do nothing here and just relax and enjoy the oxygen-rich air by sitting in your resort. Even activities such as hiking, trekking, and rope traversing can also be done here. Therefore, making it an ideal place for peace and adventure seekers.</p>\r\n<p>Now you finally know that Kolakham, even though a small beautiful hamlet, has many attractive things to offer to the tourists. Now if you are in too much hurry to go there, but don\'t yet know how to travel from NJP to Kolakham, let us guide you from first to last.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Kolakham by Road</h2>\r\n<p>There is no bus service available from NJP to Kolakham. Even any shared vehicles don\'t run from NJP to Kolakham. As a result, it becomes a huge drawback for someone.</p>\r\n<p>The only option is to hire a vehicle from New Jalpaiguri and Siliguri. While hiring a vehicle, drivers usually ask for high fares for NJP to Kolakham. &nbsp;As a result, those who don&\'t know the exact price can get cheated. To avoid this situation, we always recommend you to opt for a pre-booked car from a trusted agency like Himalayan Wheels.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Kolakham by Train</h2>\r\n<p>Kolakham does not have a train station. The nearest station of the hamlet is New Jalpaiguri Junction and the distance between them is approximately 108 km. After reaching NJP, you have to opt for a pre-booked car.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Kolakham by Air</h2>\r\n<p>The nearest airport of Kolakham is Bagdogra which is 103 km away from this beautiful town. Bagdogra is nicely connected with many national airports such as Kolkata, Chennai, Mumbai. After reaching Bagdogra, you can free-book a cab from us and we will drop you to Kolakham comfortably.</p>\r\n<h2>How to Return from Kolakham</h2>\r\n<p>You have successfully reached Kolakham, enjoyed the beauty of this astonishing hamlet and now you are worried about your return. Don\'t worry, even we are there to help you. After pre-booking our car rental service, we will drop you to your desired location. And most importantly, our drivers are highly skilled and well behaved which is enough to make your returning journey smooth. So why are you waiting? Make a plan to visit Kolakham and don\'t forget to opt for our highly convenient car rental service.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:01:33', '2019-07-09 06:08:23', NULL),
(7, 4, 11, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Latpanchar</h2>\r\n<p>Situated at an elevation of 550 ft, Latpanchar is a mesmerizing mirror of natural beauty. It is the highest point of Mahananda Wildlife Sanctuary with a magnificent view of the Teesta River and green forests around it. The place is an offbeat destination, but recently gaining popularity among tourists due to the birding activities and a thick air with a fragrance of flowers.</p>\r\n<p>Surrounded by dense mixed wet forest, Latpanchar is a less trodden village with a little population. And it is an ideal place for them who want to escape from the hustle and bustle of city life and want to spend some time close to nature. Now if your plan is to start your journey from NJP, you have come in the bright place as we are going to discuss the possible mediums needed to reach there. But first, let&#39;s talk about the attractive places the hamlet has to offer.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Offer in Latpanchar</h2>\r\n<p>Alpha Dara View Point is one of the attractive places in Latpanchar. Experience the scenic beauty of surrounding valleys, the peak of Mt. Kanchenjunga and enjoy the scenic view of Teesta River flowing as far as Haldibari.</p>\r\n<p>Latpanchar can be called a bird&#39;s paradise as it is full of various birds. Enjoy the beauty of 240 various species of birds such as Burn Swallow, laughing thirst, Sunbird, Scarlet minivet, Minla, Eagles, Woodpeckers, Kingfisher, Robin, Rufous Necked Hornbill, etc.</p>\r\n<p>Get a chance to see a mysterious reptile named salamander which was even present in dinosaur&#39;s age. Try to look this reptile closely and wonder about what makes them unique.</p>\r\n<p>Namthing Lake is another attractive place in Latpanchar. The atmosphere of the lake is enough to soothe your mind and heart. Surrounded by dense pine trees, this lake is the home of different type of beautiful birds and the mysterious salamanders.</p>\r\n<p>Located about 5 km away from Latpanchar, Ahal Dara View Point is the perfect place to see the sunrise from the snow-capped Mt. Kanchenjunga peak. Be amazed by the enchanting beauty of the surrounding places from there.</p>\r\n<p>Now if you have finally made your mind to visit this mini heaven of Earth, let us describe how to travel from NJP to Latpanchar, NJP to Latpanchar taxi fare first.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Latpanchar by Road</h2>\r\n<p>Bus service is not available from NJP to Latpanchar. As a result, one might find it difficult to travel to this particular place. Shared jeeps or taxis are available from Siliguri only. After reaching Siliguri, you have to take a shared taxi to Kalijora. Siliguri to Kalijhora taxi fare is not much but you have to bear a lot of hassles. From Kalijhora, you have to get a shared taxi again to reach Latpanchar.</p>\r\n<p>To travel from NJP to Latpanchar, a private or pre-booked car is the right choice. NJP to Latpanchar car fare is high if you pre-book them. Some of them only go to Kalijhora. From there, you again have to take a car. The journey is quite troublesome but if you opt for our car rental service to travel from NJP to Latpanchar, we will pick you from NJP and will drop you at your desired place in Latpanchar. And the car fare from NJP to Latpanchar is also quite cheap here at Himalayan Wheels.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Latpanchar by Train</h2>\r\n<p>You cannot go by train from NJP to Latpanchar as Latpanchar has no railway stations. The nearest railway station of the village is New Jalpaiguri Junction which is approximately 45 km away. This is not good for someone who hates to travel by bus.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Latpanchar by Air</h2>\r\n<p>Traveling from NJP to Latpanchar by air is also impossible, as there is no airport in Latpanchar. The nearest airport of the village is Bagdogra and the distance between them is approximately 49 km.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, you have come to know all the details related to traveling to Latpanchar. We have even informed you about the problems you are going to face while traveling. The unavailability of buses or shared taxis is a huge drawback. And that is why to solve your problem we have introduced a car rental service from New Jalpaiguri. All you have to do is that just pre-book our car and we will be there to pick you up.</p>\r\n<p>Returning from Latpanchar is not a problem too. Himalayan Wheels also has a car rental service directly from Latpanchar to NJP. So, why are you waiting? Make a plan to visit this mesmerizing Hamlet soon with your near and dear ones.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:01:40', '2019-07-09 06:20:56', NULL),
(8, 4, 12, '<h2>How to travel from NJP to Lolegaon</h2>\r\n<p>If you are finding peace and want to enjoy the breathtaking beauty of nature, you should at least travel once to Lolegaon. It is a magnificent Lepcha hamlet with a population of just 5000 people. At an altitude of 1675 meters, it is located at the extreme end of the Himalayan ridge in the Kalimpong District of West Bengal. It is undoubtedly nature\'s paradise, known for its simplicity and the panoramic view of Mount Kanchenjunga. There are also many attractive places located in Lolegaon, let\'s dive into all of them one by one and later get to know about all the mediums needed to reach there.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Lolegaon</h2>\r\n<p>Lolegaon is full of attractive places and Neora Valley Nation Park is one of them. If you are a nature and bird lover, this park is a must-visit destination. Feel the solace of nature and get to know about a cute creature named Red Panda. The park is also a home of various flora and fauna.</p>\r\n<p>Get closer to a Buddhist Monastery and feel the presence of Lord Buddha everywhere at Lava Jamgyong Kongtrul Monastery. Know this oldest Tibetan architecture and get an astonishing panoramic view of the entire village as well as of the mountains.</p>\r\n<p>Experience walking on a 180 meters long wooden tree-top bridge hanging from one tree to another. View the beauty of the forest from a reasonable height and feel the continuous swing of the bridge.</p>\r\n<p>Get the majestic view of Kanchenjunga and Mount Everest from wooden hilltop named Jhandi Dara. Get a chance to experience the most cherished memory of your life by seeing the sunrise over the snow peaked Kanchenjungha.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Lolegaon by Road</h2>\r\n<p>Lolegaon is nicely connected with NJP and many other places by road. Private and many government buses are available from Siliguri and the bus will go to your desired location via Kalimpong and lava.</p>\r\n<p>You can book private taxis too from NJP to Loleg