(10, 4, 15, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Pelling</h2>\r\n<p>Sikkim has many attractive places to offer for the thirsty nature lovers and Pelling is one of them. It is a small beautiful town, situated amidst the dense forest of pine trees in the West Sikkim. Nestled at an altitude of 2100 meters, it is a blessing of nature. The interest of tourists to visit the town is increasing day by day. As a result, many new hotels are being constructed and new roads are being made too. If you are planning to visit Sikkim from NJP, Pelling should be in your must-visit list.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Pelling</h2>\r\n<p>Pelling does not lack any attractive places. There are many scenic places present to attract tourists. Sangachoeling Monastery is the best one where you can come closer to spirituality and get a chance to know Buddhism. This ancient monastery was built in the 17th century where many Buddhists or even many travelers seek blessings. Witness the charm of a breathtaking waterfall names Changery Fall and get amazed by watching it, coming out from a dense forest. The height of the waterfall is 300m and it exactly looks like a white line. Explore the other decade-old monasteries like Pemayangtse Monastery, Dubdi Monastery, and Tashiding Monastery and be amazed by seeing their style of construction. Visit one of the most beautiful waterfalls of Sikkim, Kanchenjunga Fall and explore the astonishing beauty of it. Get closer to nature, by walking on the rocky path leading to the fall. Khecheopalri Lake is a beautiful place where Tranquility And Divinity Blend. A serene and scenic attraction of Pelling, Kechoparli Lake is the prime example where beauty and religious belief meet.</p>\r\n<p>Now maybe you are craving to visit this picturesque town as soon as possible. Please keep patience, as we are now going to discuss the medium needed to go there.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Pelling by Road</h2>\r\n<p>The direct bus service is not available from NJP to Pelling and this could be a problem for someone who prefers the bus instead of cab or taxi. The shared vehicle is not available too. As a result, you have to come to Siliguri first then to Jorethang and from there you have to go to Pelling by care. The journey is full of hassles and one might get exhausted. And that is why with Himalayan Wheels car rental service, you can easily rent a car from NJP to Pelling at a reasonable price.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Pelling by Train</h2>\r\n<p>Pelling does not lack any beautiful places but a rail station. The nearest rail station in this town is New Jalpaiguri Junction at a distance of 137 km. As you can see, traveling from NJP to Pelling by train is impossible. This can be a huge drawback for someone who always prefers the train journey.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Pelling by Air</h2>\r\n<p>The nearest airport of Pelling is Bagdogra and the distance between Bagdogra to Pelling is approximately 140 km. Due to the lack of an airport, Pelling can&#39;t be reached by air.</p>\r\n<p>As you can see, visiting this magnificent town of West Sikkim is not an easy job. You have to bear all the troubles in order to enjoy the beauty of nature it offers. Whether you try to visit it by road, by air or by train, the journey is not going to be smooth. And this is why we are offering a convenient car rental service to you from NJP to Pelling. The process of booking our car is completely hassle-free and we are just one phone call away from you. You can even pre-book our car while returning and we assure you that your journey with us will be safe and comfortable.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:02:07', '2019-07-09 06:54:30', NULL),
(11, 4, 16, '<h2>How to Travel From NJP to Ravangla</h2>\r\n<p>South Sikkim has many attractive towns to offer to the tourists and Ravangla is one of them. Located at the elevation of 8000 ft, it offers an astonishing view of Mt. Kanchenjunga, Mt. Pandim, Mt. Sinialchu and Mt. Kabru. The city is also known for thousands of attractive flowers which usually blossom in the month of April and May. Now if you are planning to from NJP to Ravangla there to spend some days, let\'s know about some attractive places the town has.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Ravangla</h2>\r\n<p>Buddha Park is a relatively new construction in Ravangla. The construction work completely finished in 2013 but it is now already the main attraction of Ravangla. The statue is 130 ft tall which is enough to amaze every tourist. The park is huge and peaceful. One can discover the inner peace here and the view of the surrounding is quite breathtaking too.</p>\r\n<p>Sikkim has many beautiful monasteries to offer for pilgrims and tourists.</p>\r\n<p>Palchen Choeling Monastic Institute is one of them which is a home of 5000 Buddhist monks. Built-in 1955, this ancient monastery is the symbol of ancient architecture. You can visit the monastery and can learn the way the monks live there.</p>\r\n<p>Doling Gompa is another ancient monastery founded in 1718. It has a special spiritual significance. According to a religious belief, the rock in front of the Gompa holds the footprint of the horse of local Guardian deity and Dorjelingpa. According to a legend, descendants of Lama Rigdzin take care of the monastery and its surrounding grounds.</p>\r\n<p>Rayong sunrise viewpoint is another attractive place. From here, you can view a breathtaking sunrise from the Cholamountains. At an elevation of 6700 feet, you can get a panoramic view of Ravangla and its neighboring mountains. And we know you can&rsquo;t deny visiting the place after hearing it.</p>\r\n<p>The town has many other attractive places to offer too. But now let&#39;s talk about the medium it needed to travel from NJP to Ravangla.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Ravangla by Road</h2>\r\n<p>There are no buses available from NJP to Ravangla. As a result, you have to find other options like a private car or shared taxis. During your journey from NJP to Ravangla, you have to come to Siliguri first to get a shared jeep. Shared Jeeps are usually available at beside Tenzing Norgay Bus Stations. But one problem of taking a shared cab is that it stops at Namchi Bazar due to permit issues. From Namchi Bazar, you have to take a cab to finally reach Ravangla. The journey is a complete tiresome for everyone.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Ravangla by Train</h2>\r\n<p>Travelling from NJP to Ravangla is impossible as there is no railway station in Ravangla. New Jalpaiguri Station itself is the nearest railway station of Ravangla. The distance between them is approximately 121 km. This can be problematic for someone who can\'t bear a journey by bus.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Ravangla by Air</h2>\r\n<p>Ravangla does not have an airport either. The nearest airport Bagdogra is at a distance of approximately 135 km. It is a four hours journey by car from Bagdogra to Ravangla.</p>\r\n<p>As you can see, travelling from NJP to Ravangla is full of hassles. To rescue you from this situation, Himalayan Wheels is offering a car rental service. Here you can pre-book a cab to directly travel from NJP to Ravangla. Returning process is also quite easy. You can now also pre-book us while returning after enjoying every bit of this beautiful city.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:02:24', '2019-07-09 07:02:39', NULL),
(12, 4, 17, '<h2>How to travel from NJP to Sittong</h2>\r\n<p>You may be heard about the beauty of Kurseung or Darjeeling. Maybe you would have been there already. But have you heard about Sittong? A scenic Hamlet which is full of serenity and charm.It is just as beautiful as Darjeeling or Kerseung. It is a wonderland nestled in the lap of mountains with just about 33 km distance from Darjeeling. The village is also known as the Orange village and this offbeat destination with its tea gardens, snow-covered peaks, toy trains, and ancient architectures will surely soothe your mind and give a lifetime memory to cherish for.</p>\r\n<p>Now if you are planning to visit this astonishing hamlet but don\'t yet know how to reach there, we are here to help you out. But first, have a look at the attractive places Sittong can offer to the thirsty travelers.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to visit at Sittong</h2>\r\n<p>Sittong has many attractive places to offer to travelers and the other name of it is &quot;The orange village&quot;. please your eyes by seeing many orange trees full of oranges during winter. A church, at first built with bamboo, now turned into a brick and mortar building, can fill your mind with happiness and peace. The beautiful view of the surrounding hills from there is worth mentioning.</p>\r\n<p>Feel the presence of Buddha even in the monastery constructed with bamboo and mud. The scenic view of Kanchenjungha from this monastery is a bonus for tourists. Get to know more about Mangpoo, which is just 8km away from Sittong and know why it was praised by our famous poet Rabindranath Tagore. Enjoy watching various birds and butterflies in Mahananda Wildlife Sanctuary. Get a chance to know more about the villagers, their lifestyle and how they enjoy their life in a simple manner.</p>\r\n<h3>NJP to Sittong by Road</h3>\r\n<p>The distance between NJP and Sittong is just 31.7 km. There is no bus available from NJP to Sittong. Till now there is even no shared jeep or taxi available directly from NJP to Sittong. You have to take a shared jeep or taxi to Kurseung first after then, take a taxi to reach Sittong. This process is full of hassles and takes too much time. It is enough to kill your enjoyment of visiting Sittong.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Sittong by train</h2>\r\n<p>In Sittong, there is no railway station. NJP is the nearest railway station of Sittong. As a result, you can&#39;t go there by train. It is quite problematic because many people usually prefer to travel by train instead of bus.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Sittong by Air</h2>\r\n<p>If you are planning to go to Sittong by aeroplane, you will be highly disappointed to know that it has no airport either. The nearest airport in the village is Bagdogra which is around 34 km away from Sittong. But if you are planning to visit Sittong by road, you can still opt for our car rental service as we also offer pre-booked car from Bagdogra to Sittong.</p>\r\n<p>In this situation, the best option is to take a reserved car. But again while you seek for reserved car, drivers can ask for the high fare and this could be quite tiresome to bargain with the drivers. As a result, to rescue you from this situation, we have opened a car rental service directly from NJP to Sittong. Just call us one day before your scheduled journey and we will pick and drop you to your desired destination.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:02:17', '2019-07-09 07:11:30', NULL);
