(13, 4, 18, '<h2>How to travel from NJP to Rishop</h2>\r\n<p>Rishop, also known as Rishyap or Risop, is a small touristy village amidst lava and Lolegaon. Situated at an elevation of 2951 meters, Rishop is a blessing for adventure seekers as well as for nature lovers. This beautiful hamlet is 32 km away from Kalimpong and just 9 km road distance away from Lava. The village is too calm and far away from city crowds. The rays of the sun, clouds, mesmerizing Himalaya and dense forests create a magical atmosphere in the village. At night, the sky looks completely different, where stars are twinkling, the beautiful lights which come from Gangtok and Pedong bellow are visible from this village. Nathu La pass and Jalep La pass are also partially visible in a distant horizon from Rishop. Altogether, Rishop offers a scenic and astonishing beauty of nature to the travelers. And if you want to travel from NJP to Rishop, we are going to describe all the possible methods to reach there.</p>\r\n<p>Blessed with rich flora and fauna, this newly discovered travel destination is surrounded with pine, birch, rhododendrons and orchid&#39;s forests. One can find inner peace and can get a breathtaking view of snow-peaked mountains. Now let&#39;s have a look at some of the attractive places Rishop has to offer.</p>\r\n<h2>Attractive Places in Rishop</h2>\r\n<p>Tiffandra viewpoint is a renowned place in Rishop. It is a viewpoint to watch the breathtaking view of Sunrise and Sunset. This is the perfect place to see the snowcapped mountains of Himalaya and surrounding valleys.</p>\r\n<p>Shiva Buddha Temple is the most unique and attractive places in Rishop. It is a temple or you can say a monastery, where two religions meet. After climbing up to the red staircase, you will finally witness a view of two different gods of two different religions are mounted side by side.</p>\r\n<p>Just 4 km away from Rishop, kolakham is an attractive village with many attractive places. Witness the breathtaking view of changery fall, the sweet sound of the falling water, and the mesmerizing view of the surrounding rocks, which are capable to soothe your mind.</p>\r\n<p>At a distance of 11 km from Rishop, lava is also a village full of attractive places. Lava Monastery is the prime example of Lava&#39;s attraction. This monastery was built in 1871 and the habitant of more than 110 monks. If you are curious enough to know the lifestyle and culture of these monks, you can surely visit this monastery.</p>\r\n<p>Now we finally know some of the fascinating places in Rishop. Let us talk about the transportation system needed from NJP to Rishop.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Rishop by Road</h2>\r\n<p>From New Jalpaiguri Rishop is at a distance of 110 km via Kalimpong and 120 km away via Gorubathan. There are no buses available from NJP to Rishop. Government or public buses don&#39;t even run from Siliguri to Rishop. As a result, those, who want to save some money, can&#39;t get the service.</p>\r\n<p>Shared jeeps are not available either. Therefore the only option is that you take a private or pre-booked car to travel from NJP to Rishop. It usually takes more than 3 hours to reach Rishop. You can even opt for a car from NJP to Kalimpong and after then take another vehicle to reach Rishop. As you can see, you have to change many vehicles to finally reach Rishop and the journey could be quite tiresome for someone.</p>\r\n<h3>NJP to Rishop by Train</h3>\r\n<p>Rishop has no specific railway station. The nearest rail station of this hamlet is New Jalpaiguri Junction. The distance between them is approximately 107km. NJP is well connected with many other big cities. After reaching NJP by train, you can opt for a car rental service provider such as Himalayan Wheels to directly travel from NJP to Rishop.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Rishop by Air</h2>\r\n<p>The nearest airport of this beautiful hamlet is Bagdogra. At a distance of 120km from Rishop, Bagdogra Airport is nicely connected with many other states. After reaching Bagdogra, there are plenty of taxis available to reach Rishop. Drivers usually ask for the high fare and they will not give you any scope to negotiate the price.</p>\r\n<p>Therefore the best option is to opt for Himalayan Wheels car rental service. Our price of the car is within your budget and we always provide an experienced driver so that your journey becomes smooth.</p>\r\n<h2>How to Return from Rishop</h2>\r\n<p>Returning is not a headache either. We also offer car rental services from Rishop to NJP. Just call us after enjoying the fascinating Rishop and we will pick and drop you to your desired location.</p>\r\n', NULL, 'Do you need any information about travelling from NJP to Rishop? Here in this article we have discussed all the possible ways to reach Rishop from NJP.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:02:33', '2019-07-09 08:36:40', NULL),
(14, 4, 19, '<h2>How to travel from NJP to Jhalong</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are a lot of attractive places in Dooars and Jhalong is one of them. Just 99 km away from Siliguri, this beautiful hamlet is a lesser-trodden offbeat wonder of Dooars, situated in the Kalimpong District of West Bengal. Nestled on the bank of Eastern Himalaya on the bank of the Jaldhaka River, this hamlet is ideal for all the adventure seekers and tourists because of its astonishing beauty and mesmerizing travel destinations. Now if your plan is to travel from NJP to Jhalong but knows nothing about how to reach there, we are here to guide you from first to last. But first, let&#39;s talk about some of the attractive places in Jhalong.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Jhalong</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Jaldhaka Hydel Project on the Jaldhaka River is one of the major attractions of Jhalong. This hydroelectric project is the first of its kind where the tourist has permission to visit the dam. As the dam is close to the Bhutan border, it acts as a bridge to connect India and Bhutan. You even get a mesmerizing view of mountains and a lot of birds can also be seen flying above the dam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bindu Dam is another attractive place in Jhalong. It was built to operate water supply to Jaldhaka Hydel Project. Situated just 8 km away from Jhalong, Bindu Dam also offers an astonishing view of snow-peaked mountains. Various beautiful birds can also be seen from here.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>NJP to Jhalong by Road</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to travel from NJP to Jhalong, you have to come to Siliguri first by taking an auto. From there, North Bengal State Transport Corporation Buses, Bhutan Govt. Buses, Mini Buses, Assam Transport Corporation Buses, Private Buses, and Taxi usually run from Siliguri to Jhalong. And it usually takes two and a half hours to reach Jhalong.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Shared taxi or car is not available from NJP to Jhalong as it is an offbeat destination. Although you can hire a car from NJP to Jhalong, drivers usually ask for high fares and it will be hard for you to negotiate the price.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>NJP to Jhalong by Train</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The nearest rail station of Jhalong is New Malbazar Junction at a distance of 26 km. This rail station is nicely connected with New Jalpaiguri Junction and New Jalpaiguri is connected with various major cities of India. After travelling from NJP to Jhalong, you have to again opt for a taxi to finally reach in Jhalong. With your heavy luggage, it is hard to change vehicles.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>NJP to Jhalong by Air</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Jhalong does not have an airport and the nearest one is Bagdogra at a distance of 104 km. This airport is nicely connected with various major airports of the country. As a result, after landing at Bagdogra you have to hire a taxi to Jhalong. Here arises a problem too. As they ask for high fare it could be a little problematic to you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To sum it up, the journey from NJP to Jhalong is not smooth as you might have been thought earlier. While traveling on the bus, you have to change many vehicles with your heavy luggage and even when you opt for the train, the journey is again not smooth. Therefore, to solve your problems, here at Himalayan Wheels, we offer a car rental service for you directly from NJP to Jhalong. The cars are quite good for travel and fit everyone&rsquo;s budget. And most importantly, you can even return with us.</p>\r\n', NULL, 'Here in this article we have given a complete guide to travel from NJP to Jhalong. Just click the link to  know more about it.', NULL, 10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60, 70, 80, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-24 11:59:13', '2019-07-11 11:31:51', NULL),
(15, 4, 20, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Lataguri</h2>\r\n<p>If you think that Jalpaiguri has nothing to offer for tourists, you may have not heard about Latarguri then. It is a small town, situated in the Jalpaiguri district of West Bengal. Located on the outskirt of Gorumara national park, Lataguri is the perfect combination of attractive places with dense forests. Gorumara National Park, Chapramari National park and Buxa Tiger Reserves add more charms to these towns. Now if you are planning to reach this charming town from NJP to Gorumara, let us describe the attractive places in Lataguri first.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Lataguri</h2>\r\n<p>Gorumara National Park is one of the attractive places in Lataguri. Spread over an area of 80 sq km, the place is mostly famous for its rich flora and fauna, especially for Asiatic one-horned rhino. The park is also popular for other mammals, insects, reptiles and birds, such as royal Bengal tigers, Indian hornbills, and mighty Asian elephants, Indian Wild Dogs, Giant Squirrels, Wild boars, deer, cobra, python, woodpeckers and many other animals. Because of its attractiveness and variety of wildlife, Gorumara National Park has already become a must-visit place for tourists.</p>\r\n<p>Chapramari Wildlife Sanctuary is another touristy place. Located at a distance of about 20 km from the Gorumara National Park, this Wildlife Sanctuary is another prime example of nature&rsquo;s excellence. Nestled in the backdrop of Kanchenjunga and other Himalayan peaks, one can see many wild animals like elephants, gaur, leopards, deer, etc.</p>\r\n<p>The bank of the Murti River is also a fascinating place to visit in Lataguri. The jaw-dropping view of the surrounding places and many thirty wild animals are coming to fulfill their thirst makes the river a must-visit place for travelers.</p>\r\n<p>There are limited tigers alive in this world. And in order to save them, Buxa Tiger Reserve gives shelter to this amazing animal. You can see plenty of other animals such as elephants, bison, sambar, barking hog, deer, wild boars, wild buffaloes, and leopards.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Lataguri by Road</h2>\r\n<p>The bus service is not available from NJP to Lataguri. As a result, you first have to come to Siliguri. You can get a bus from PC Mittal Bus Stand which will run via Sevoke Road. Alternatively, you can opt for a bus from Tenzing Norgay Bus Terminal. The buses from this terminal usually run to Siliguri and after then you have to change the bus to reach Lataguri.</p>\r\n<p>The distance between NJP to Gorumara is approximately 28 km and it usually takes 2 hours to reach depending on the road conditions. Shared jeep or taxi is not available from NJP to Gorumara. But a pre-booked car is available from NJP to Gorumara.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Lataguri by Train</h2>\r\n<p>Lataguri does not have any specific Railway Station. New Jalpaiguri itself is the nearest railway station of this town. As a result, one can&rsquo;t visit this town by train. After reaching New Jalpaiguri junction, you can book a pre-booked car from Himalayan Wheels to safely travel from NJP to Lataguri.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Lataguri by Air</h2>\r\n<p>Lataguri does not have an airport and the nearest airport of the town is Bagdogra. Visiting the town by air is impossible but after reaching Bagdogra you take our pre-booked car to directly travel from Bagdogra to Lataguri.</p>\r\n<p>As you can see, traveling to Lataguri from NJP is little troublesome while you take a bus. Pre-paid taxis also charge for more if the drivers find you as a newcomer. We, at Himalayan Wheels, offer the best car fare from NJP to Lataguri. Here you don\'t have to change any vehicles to travel from NJP to Gorumara. Just a phone call and we are here to help you and if you have any inquiries related to car fare and cars, you are welcome to contact us.</p>', NULL, 'Lataguri has many attractive places to visit. And in this article we have discussed about some attractive places of Lataguri, how to travel from NJP to Lataguri and many more.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:02:49', '2019-07-11 11:36:35', NULL),
(16, 4, 21, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Murti</h2>\r\n<p>Have a plan to visit Gorumara but don\'t know about Murti yet? Well, Murti is a little place situated between the Chapramari Forest and Gourumara National Park. Situated along the bank of the River Murti, Murti as a place is a scenic beauty of Earth. The surrounding places like Gorumara National Park and Capramari Wildlife Sanctuary are worth to visit while staying in Murti. The glittering flow of the Murti River and the astonishing scenic landscape has made this place a must-visit place in Dooars. Now if your journey starts from NJP to Murti, you have come in the right place. But first, have a look at some of the attractive places located in Murti.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Murti</h2>\r\n<p>The Murti River itself is one of the attractive places in Murti. Enjoy the astonishing beauty of surrounding places of the river and feel the calmness of its bank. Take a bath in the river and get refreshed from all the troubles of your life. Even, enjoy the jaw-dropping view of the wild animals which usually come to drink water here.</p>\r\n<p>Visit Gorumara National Park and witness some of the unique wild animals like One-horned Rhinoceros, Royan Bengal Tiger, Asian Elephants and many more. Take a jeep safari to go deep to the forest and come closer to these wild animals.</p>\r\n<p>Visit the nearest Chapramari Wildlife Sanctuary which is another touristy place. Located at a distance of about 20 km from the Gorumara National Park, get a chance to see some wild animals like elephants, gaur, leopards, deer, etc. An astonishing view of Mounts in the backdrop is a bonus from here.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Murti by Road</h2>\r\n<p>Bus services are not available directly from NJP to Murti. From NJP you have to come in Siliguri&rsquo;s PC Mittal Bus Stand on Sevoke Road. From here the buses usually leave for Malbazar and Chalsa. Get a Chalsa bus and after reaching Chalsa, get another bus to finally reach Murti. The process of t