enient way to reach there comfortably.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:02:56', '2019-07-11 11:41:46', NULL),
(17, 4, 22, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Samsing</h2>\r\n<p>Situated at an elevation of 3000 ft, Samsing is a small touristy village located in the foothills of Eastern Himalaya of the Dooars region. After driving through some of the most beautiful tea gardens and valleys, one can finally reach Samsing. The magnificent mountains in the backdrop, vast stretches of green fields, dense forest and a bunch of attractive places attract a lot of tourists to visit this picturesque hamlet. Now, if you are one of them who got attracted and want to spend some peaceful days in the lap of nature, and even want to know how to travel from NJP to Samsing, you have come in a right place. But first, let us showcase some of the attractive places in Samsing.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Samsing</h2>\r\n<p>Neora Valley National Park is the main attraction of tourists in Samsing. Blessed with rich flora and fauna, Neora Valley National Park is famous for many rare species and Red Panda is one of them.</p>\r\n<p>Just 2km away from Samsing, Rocky Island is also a touristy place. Located on the bank of the Murti River, Rocky Island is an attractive place. The place is full of scenic beauty and many big rocks scattered here and there add more charm to the place. You can even get a breathtaking view of the Himalayan range from a place named Tree Fern Point.</p>\r\n<p>Shasmahal is a nearby village of Samsing where you can see many orange orchards. The village completely changes its color into orange during the orange season. The beauty of the surrounding places of the village is worth mentioning too.</p>\r\n<p>Faribasti is another nearby place to Samsing. It is a village with not more than 50 households and you can get an intense panoramic view of the entire Dooars region from here. Every household has beautiful flower gardens, therefore, making the village too attractive to the tourists.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Samsing by Road</h2>\r\n<p>Bus services are not directly available from NJP to Samsin