(18, 4, 23, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Suntalekhola</h2>\r\n<p>You may have heard about Samsing and many attractive places it offers to the tourists. But here let&#39;s talk about Suntalekhola, a picturesque hamlet in the Kalimpong District of West Bengal. Located at an altitude of 650 to 950 meters, the name of this beautiful hamlet comes from a small stream named SuntaleyKhola. Surrounded by a dense forest, the green patch on the left side of the way to Suntalekhola is mesmerizing and you can see various birds and butterflies. If you are planning to travel from NJP to Suntalekhola to enjoy this scenic beauty, let us describe some of the attractive places in Suntalekhola first.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Suntalekhola</h2>\r\n<p>Suntalekhola and its nearby places have many attractive things to offer to the tourists. Get a chance to walk on the Hanging Bridge in Suntalekhola and enjoy the beauty of surrounding tress while walking. Spend some time on the Hanging Bridge and pleasure your eyes by watching the beautiful river flowing under the bridge.</p>\r\n<p>Faribasti is a nearby village of Suntalekhola. It is a beautiful hamlet with just 50 households. You will get amazed by seeing that all the houses are well maintained and every house has a beautiful flower garden.</p>\r\n<p>At a distance of just 5km from Suntalekhola, Samsing is another picturesque village. Samsing Neora Valley National Park is the most popular one among tourists. Blessed with rich flora and fauna, Neora Valley is quite popular for Red Panda. Samsing View Point is another attractive place where you can get a mesmerizing view of the river Murti and its surrounding places.</p>\r\n<p>Rocky Island is another attractive place located just 3 km away from Samsing. The place is beautiful and you can see many big rocks here and there. There is a place named Tree Fern Point from where you can get a breathtaking view of Himalayan Range.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Suntalekhola by Road</h2>\r\n<p>To travel from 