(19, 4, 24, '<h2>How to travel form NJP to Bindu</h2>\r\n<p>In Dooars, there are plenty of offbeat destinations and Bindu is undoubtedly one of them. A small village at an altitude of 600 meters, on the Indo-Bhutan border, this beautiful hamlet is famous for cardamom plantation, mesmerizing nature, and river Jaldhaka. Bindu is beautifully located in the Kalimpong District among the high Himalayan Mountains and the Jaldhaka River flowing through the valley which makes a natural border between India and Bhutan. Sited on the foothills of Himalaya, Bindu is undoubtedly a mesmerizing place to enjoy natural beauty. Now if you want to enjoy every Bindu has to offer but don&#39;t know how to reach there from NJP to Bindu, let us guide you. But first, know some of the reasons for what you should visit Bindu.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Bindu</h2>\r\n<p>Bindu Dam is one of the attractive places in Bindu. It was built on the Jaldhaka River to supply water to Jaldhaka Hydel Project. This Dam is a habitant of many beautiful birds and therefore it is a paradise for nature lovers.</p>\r\n<p>Jaldhaka Hydel project is the first of its kind in entire India where tourists have permission to closely see the dam. During the season of winter, it also attracts various birds from various places thus making it a must-visit place for bird enthusiasts. The dam even works as a bridge between India and Bhutan.</p>\r\n<p>The Godak Village is a must-visit place near Bindu. Just 15 km away from Bindu, this village is popularly known for a tribal goddess. Many devotees worship the goddess river which originates from a rock that never dries.</p>\r\n<p>Famous for medicinal plants, garibas is also an attractive place to visit near Bindu. Diascorrea Plantation can be seen all around the village and this makes the village to look beautiful. For the enthusiasts of trees, the place is undoubtedly heaven.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Bindu by Road</h2>\r\n<p>If your plan is to travel from NJP to Bindu, first come t