(22, 4, 27, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Gajoldoba</h2>\r\n<p>Gajoldoba is a small picturesque village in Jalpaiguri District of Dooars region. Between the Mahananda River and the Teesta River, Gajoldoba is surrounded by dense Baikunthopur Forest. The astonishing view of the tall mountains and many attractive places is making Gajoldoba a must-visit tourist spot rapidly. A mega tourism project is going on in Gajoldoba with a promise of making Gajoldoba a hot tourist destination in the near future. Now if you are planning to travel from NJP to Gajoldoba but don&#39;t know how to reach there, you have come in the right place. Before talking about how to reach there, first, let us showcase some of the attractive places in Gajoldoba.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Gajoldoba</h2>\r\n<p>Gajoldoba barrage is the most famous place to visit in Gajoldoba. Located above the Teesta river, this barrage gives a beautiful view of Mount Kanchenjunga. Surrounded by dense Baikunthopur Forest, this place is too ideal to spend some quality time with nature as the place stays completely silent all the time.</p>\r\n<p>For the enthusiasts of birds, Gajoldoba is the must-visit place. You will never get tired by watching the birds like Indian cormorant, Northern Lapwing, River Lapwing, Grey Headed Lapwing, Indian Pond Heron, Common Teal, Tufted Duck, Bar Headed Goose and many more.</p>\r\n<p>In Gajoldoba, there is a mega project going on named as &quot;BhorerAlo&quot;. Tourist can vail 3-star hotels, 4-star hotels, 9 Hole Golf course, Govt Tourist Lodge, Lifestyle Clubs along with many other interesting aspects for tourists.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Gajoldoba by Road</h2>\r\n<p>Gajoldoba or BhorerAlo is just 19 km away from NJP. There is no bus available and you don&#39;t need a bus either. To travel from NJP to Gajoldoba, take a shared car, an auto or a toto to reach Ghorar More or Ashigahar and then again get a shared car to finally arrive in Gajoldoba. From NJP to Gajoldoba, the journey is full