(23, 4, 28, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Jalpaiguri</h2>\r\n<p>In the Indian state of West Bengal, a beautiful city Jalpaiguri is located on the bank of Teesta River which is the second-largest river in the West Bengal. Rich with historical and natural beauty, the city is quite popular for the view of mountain hills, mesmerizing tea gardens, and unique cultures. The nearby attractions like Gorumara National Park, Jaldapara Wildlife Sanctuary, Chapramari Wildlife Sanctuary and the bay of River Teesta is luring many travelers to visit this city. Now if you are planning a trip from NJP to Jalpaiguri and want to know how to reach there, you have come in the perfect place as we are going to discuss car fares, best car rental providers and most importantly how to reach there.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Jalpaiguri</h2>\r\n<p>The city of Jalpaiguri does not lack any attractive places. Jalpaiguri Rajbari is an ancient architecture carrying many cultural values of Jalpaiguri. The huge gate of the palace makes us wonder about the ancient techniques of the architects.</p>\r\n<p>Rajbari Dighi is another attractive place to visit near Rajbari. If you demand tranquility and peace, this place is the ideal one for you. Spend hours of time by sitting beneath trees and watch the stable water of the pond.</p>\r\n<p>Gorumara National park is an attractive tourist destination near Jalpaiguri. The main attractions of the tourists here are One-horned rhinoceros, Royal Bengal Tiger, leopard, hornbills, and a variety of birds.</p>\r\n<p>Just 25 km away from Jalpaiguri town, Jalpesh is the major attraction of Maynaguri. Thousands of tourists and devotees come here every year to take the blessing of Lord Shiva.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Jalpaiguri by Road</h2>\r\n<p>Jalpaiguri is well accessible by road. There are many buses available from New Jalpaiguri. At a distance of 42.5 km from NJP, it usually takes 1 hour 30 minutes via SH12a road to travel from NJP to Jalpaiguri. You can even opt for a b