(24, 4, 29, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Maynaguri</h2>\r\n<p>Among many other places to visit in West Bengal, Maynaguri should be in your must-visit list. Maynaguri is a tiny town located in Jalpaiguri District of West Bengal. Popularly known as &quot;The Gateway of Dooars&quot;, this town is quite popular for \"Jalpesh Mandir\" and Gorumara National Park which is located nearby the city. Now if your plan is to travel from NJP to Maynaguri, we will guide you about how to reach there, the best car rental service agency and the best car fare. But first, let us showcase some of the attractive places in Maynaguri.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Maynaguri</h2>\r\n<p>Jalpesh Mandir is one of the attractive places in Maynaguri. This holy temple of Lord Shiva attracts lakhs of devotees throughout the years. But the devotees mostly increase during the month of monsoon when lakhs of pilgrims travel together to Jalpesh to worship Lord Shiva by chanting \"Bhole Bom\". Here you can feel the presence of Lord Shiva and get lost in the dimension of spirituality.</p>\r\n<p>Khuksia Park is another attractive place in Maynaguri. This park is ideal to get relief from the stress of life. One can spend some quality time in calm, peace and in a beautiful surrounding.</p>\r\n<p>As Maynaguri is &quot;The Gateway of Dooars&quot; you can spend some quality time in Maynaguri before traveling to Dooars which is blessed with many astonishing places and rich flora and fauna.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Maynaguri by Road</h2>\r\n<p>Bus service is not directly available from NJP to Maynaguri. As a result, get an auto from New Jalpaiguri to travel up to Siliguri. In Siliguri, there are plenty of buses available for Maynaguri. The distance between Siliguri to Maynaguri is 66 km and it usually takes 2 hours to reach Maynaguri.</p>\r\n<p>A shared taxi is not available and therefore, you have to hire a private taxi. And, we always suggest you pre-book a car from Himalayan Wheels as Himalayan Wheels is the best 