(25, 4, 30, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Alipurduar</h2>\r\n<p>Nestled in the foothills of mighty Himalaya, on the bank of Kajlani River, Alipurduar is a magnificent town in the Alipurduar District of West Bengal. Surrounded by dense forest, gushing rivers and astonishing mountains, Alipurduar is undoubtedly nature&#39;s paradise. Blessed with rich flora and fauna and pleasant weather, there is no way you can ignore a trip to this magnificent town. Now, if you are attracted to this magnificent beauty and want to travel from NJP to Alipurduar, we have landed in the exact place. Here in this article, we are going to discuss about the transportation system, car fares, and best car rental provider to visit Alipurduar. But first, let\'s talk about some of the attractive places in Alipurduar.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Alipurduar</h2>\r\n<p>Alipurduar has many attractive places to offer to the tourists and the Buxa Tiger reserve is one of them. Just 10 km away from Alipurduar, Buxa Tiger reserve is a natural habitat of tiger, leopard, elephant black panther, clouded leopard, Himalayan black deer, gaur, python and, many more. As a result, tourists can see these unique wild animals closely by going there.</p>\r\n<p>Jaldapara National Park is another attractive place in Alipurduar. Situated in the foothills of Eastern Himalaya, the park is full of different wildlife. Get a chance to see one-horned rhinoceros, tigers, elephant, leopards and many more by taking a Jungle Safari. You can even get a complete view of the surrounding jungle by taking a ride on the back of an elephant.</p>\r\n<p>Buxa Fort is another attractive place to visit in Alipurduar. The place is quite popular among trekkers and even among travelers. And the fort of this place is the symbol of the Indian freedom movement.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Alipurduar by Road</h2>\r\n<p>Bus service is usually available in Alipurduar. In order to travel from NJP to Alipurdurduar, you can come to Siliguri. From there, plenty of buses available to Aripurduar. The town is about 136 km away from Siliguri and it usually takes 4 hours to reach Alipurduar from Siliguri.</p>\r\n<p>Shared Taxis are not available, therefore you have to hire a car. But we always recommend you to use our car rental service as it is cheap and convenient for everyone.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Alipurduar by Train</h2>\r\n<p>Alipurduar has its own railway station. Therefore you can directly travel from NJP to Alipurduar. But there is a problem that it is hard to maintain the timing of the train.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Alipurduar by Air</h2>\r\n<p>Alipurduar does not have an airport and Cooch Behar airport and Bagdogra airport is the nearest of the city. After arriving in Alipurduar, you can pre-book a car from Himalayan Wheels to reach Alipurduar.</p>\r\n<p>As you can see, booking a car from the Himalayan Wheels is the most simple job you have ever done. You don&#39;t have to wait, don&#39;t have to think about bargaining, just a simple call and you are done. We will be there to pick you up and drop you to your desired travel destination. So don&#39;t forget to make us your travel companion the next time you travel.</p>', NULL, 'Alipurduar has many transportation options to reach the city. Here in this article we have discussed about how to travel from NJP to Alipurduar, the taxi fare, the best car rental service provider and some of the attractive places in Alipurduar.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:04:09', '2019-07-13 06:28:46', NULL),
(26, 31, 1, '<h2>How to travel from Bagdogra to Darjeeling</h2>\r\n<p>Nestled in the foothills of mighty Himalaya, Darjeeling is a mesmerizing city in the Darjeeling District of West Bengal. The city is quite popular among tourists because of its charming weather, view of snow-peaked mountains, exquisite scenic beauty, and lush tea gardens. Situated at an elevation of 2134 meters, Darjeeling never fails to offer a complete holiday package to the travelers and thus it is called &quot;The Queen of Hill Station&quot;. Now, if you are planning to travel from Bagdogra to Darjeeling to experience its breathtaking beauty, you have come in the right place. Here we will be discussing how to reach Darjeeling, the taxi fare and the best car rental service provider you can get. But first, let&#39;s have a look at some of the attractive places Darjeeling has to offer to the thirsty travelers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Darjeeling</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Tiger Hill is one of the most famous places in Darjeeling. This peak is known for offering a spectacular view of sun-rise. This place is also ideal to enjoy the panoramic view of the entire city, the snow-peaked Mount Kanchenjunga and even Mount Everest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Darjeeling Himalayan Railway is another attraction of Darjeeling. Popularly known as &quot;Toy Train&quot;, this magnificent train runs between Darjeeling and Jalpaiguri. The spectacular view of surrounding valleys and lush tree gardens, while traveling on the train, is enough to awe all the travelers. And because of this, Unesco has declared it a &quot;World Heritage Site&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Happy Valley Tea Estate is another must-visit place in Darjeeling. This huge place is completely covered by many green tea gardens and offers a picturesque surrounding to the travelers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Darjeeling by Road</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Darjeeling is nicely connected by road and there is no problem to travel from Bagdogra to Darjeeling. But if you want to reduce the cost of your journey, take a bus or an auto from the Bagdogra market to reach Tenzing Norgay Central Bus Terminus in Siliguri. From here, you will get many buses or shared taxis which are going for Darjeeling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As you can see, you have reduced the car fare but have sacrificed your comfort. And this is why we recommend you to take a pre-booked car from Himalayan Wheels. They will not just pick you from Bagdogra but also drop you directly to Darjeeling.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Darjeeling by Train</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Darjeeling is nicely connected with other cities by train as it is a popular travel destination. After arriving Bagdogra, you can take a train from Bagdogra to Darjeeling. But if your time does not match with the train&rsquo;s scheduled timing, you will not be able to travel by train.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Darjeeling by Air</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Darjeeling does not have an airport. The nearest airport of the city is Bagdogra. At a distance of 95 km from Darjeeling, it usually takes 3 hours to reach the city from Bagdogra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As you can see, Darjeeling is hard to travel even though it is nicely connected by road or by train from Bagdogra to Darjeeling. When you opt for a shared taxi, the taxi fare is low but you have to travel to Siliguri first. When you try to travel by train, the train&#39;s timing sometimes does not match with yours. And that is why after seeing travelers&rsquo; troubles, we have opened a car rental service from Bagdogra to Darjeeling. Here you don&#39;t have to share the car with any unknown person. Just pre-book a car from Himalayan wheels and reach your destination quite comfortably.</p>\r\n', NULL, 'Darjeeling is called the queen of the hills and here we have guided you about how to travel this scenic town from Bagdogra, what is the taxi fare and what is the best car rental service in India.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:04:26', '2019-07-13 12:59:53', NULL),
(27, 31, 32, '<h2>How to travel from Bagdogra to Gangtok</h2>\r\n<p>If you are planning to experience the calmness and the beauty of a scenic city to get relief from your hectic lifestyle but know nothing about the transportation system needed to travel from Bagdogra to Gangtok, we are here to help you. Gangtok is the capital of Sikkim, a state located in northeastern India. Gangtok is usually known as the paradise of Buddhists. One can see many tourist places in Gangtok such as many Buddhist monasteries, Nathula Pass, Tsomgo Lake, etc. which make the city a must-visit destination for travelers. Situated near the eastern Himalayan range, the city is a perfect example of a modern, resort town style with ancient spiritual beliefs and impressive natural heritage.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Gangtok</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Just 35 km away from Gangtok, Tsogmo Lake is an attractive place to visit in Gangtok. The lake is famous for its color-changing waters. In the monsoon, the water of the lake is deep and blue whereas, in the time of winter, the lake usually freezes into ice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Situated on the Indo-Chinese border, Nathula Pass is also an attractive place to visit in Gangtok. Many tourists flock here every year to enjoy the scenic beauty of the waterfalls that gush along the way from Gangtok to Nathu La. This place is also ideal to enjoy the snow-peaked mountains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Just 24 km away from Gangtok, you should not miss visiting Rumtek Monastery. As it is the most sacred monasteries in Sikkim, people from all around the world come here to take blessings of the Lord Buddha.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Gangtok by Road</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The bus service is available from Bagdogra to Gangtok. It usually takes 4 to 5 hours to reach Gangtok depending on the road condition. But we always recommend you to get a Sikkim registered vehicle because only they have the permission to enter Sikkim.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As you can see, travelling from Bagdogra to Gangtok is full of hassles. You have to change multiple vehicles due to the permit issue. But if you rent a car from Himalayan Wheels, you don&#39;t have to bear the hassle of changing cars.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Gangtok by Train</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Gangtok does not have a railway station. The nearest rail station is New Jalpaiguri Junction which is 120 km away from Gangtok. NJP connects Gangtok with India&#39;s major cities like Chennai, Kolkata, Mumbai and, many more. So after reaching NJP, you can opt for our car rental service which will drop you directly to Gangtok.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Gangtok by Air</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Gangtok does not have an airport either. The nearest airport of the city is Bagdogra which is 124 km away. This particular airport has a connection with the major cities of India. So after reaching Bagdogra, you can take a bus or taxi to travel from Bagdogra to Gangtok.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you have come to know about how to travel from Bagdogra to Gangtok and you have realized that the best car rental service provider is none other than Himalayan Wheels. Himalayan Wheels is the best choice which provides the best journey experience at a reasonable price. So, next time you travel don&#39;t forget to try us once and feel the difference.</p>\r\n', NULL, 'This article will completely guide you about how to travel from Bagdogra to Gangtok.We also mentioned  the car fare,  what are the transportation system needed to reach there and the best car rental service provides.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:04:37', '2019-07-13 13:06:10', NULL),
(28, 4, 1, '<h2>How to Travel From NJP to Darjeeling</h2>\r\n<p>Are you planning to visit the scenic beauty of Darjeeling but too worried by thinking of how to reach there? Well, you don\'t have to worry much as we, at Himalayan Wheels, are here to guide you from the beginning of your journey to your destination. Now finally, we are going to guide you like how you can go to Darjeeling by taxi, by train or by bus.</p>\r\n<p>New Jalpaiguri Railway Station or Njp is the main railway station located about 88kms south of Darjeeling. Njp serves the city Siliguri which is the largest city of North Bengal. It also serves as the entry point of Sikkim,Bhutan,Nepal, and even the northeastern states. As a result, many long-distance trains pass through that station. If you successfully arrive in NJP, there are several options to choose to reach Darjeeling such as Taxi, shared jeeps or even Darjeeling Himalayan Railway.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Darjeeling by Taxi</h2>\r\n<p>If you are planning to opt for a taxi after reaching NJP, there are hundreds of options available. Taxis are usually a small car or van which usually stay parked outside the stations. Larger vehicles are also available but the one problem is that the drivers always try their opportunistic chances. They increase the price more when it is a high tourist season. You can not even bargain due to the higher demands.</p>\r\n<p>However, if your plan is to take a reserved taxi, we always recommend that you take a pre-paid taxi. There is a prepaid taxi booth located near the taxi stand. Here the rates are fixed and you can escape from the tension of increasing price. You will get a slip as proof of advanced payment. Later all you have to do is that just hand over the slip to the driver after reaching Darjeeling. The prepaid counter usually opens at 7 am and closes by 7 pm. But here also lies many problems because the drivers they offer are inexperienced and mostly unknown to them. Are you willing to risk your life where you have other options like Himalayan Wheels?</p>\r\n<p>Here at Himalayan Wheels, we offer comfortable and convenience journey to the tourists. Here you can pre-book our vehicles and we will pick you up from where you want. And we will later drop you at your desired destinations. The process of booking our vehicles is completely hassle-free and all you have to do is a phone call to us.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Darjeeling by Shared Taxi</h2>\r\nThere are also many shared taxis available from NJP stations. Shared taxis usually two persons in the front next to the driver, four in the back seat and also four others at the rear seat. If you plan to get a shared taxi, you can a lot of problems. The vehicle will not start unless it is full of 8 to 10 passengers.You can\'t even carry heavy luggage. They usually carry luggage on the rooftop of the vehicle, therefore your costly things can get damaged.</h2>\r\n<p>If you want a little comfort, you can even book a shared a taxi to Darjeeling. You can book a seat online but the problem is that you have to come to Siliguri first. If you are little unlucky and don\'t able to get a shared jeep, you can also take an auto or cycle rickshaw to the Tenzing Norgay CentralBus Station which is also called the Siliguri main bus stand. From here we can find a lot of shared jeeps and taxis which usually are ready to go to Darjeeling. In order to make it easy to find your desired vehicles, there is a small board in front of them with the destination written on it. As you can see, the process is a little problematic.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Darjeeling by Train</h2>\r\n<p>You can travel to Darjeeling by train too. Darjeeling Himalayan Railway offers a toy train service from NJP and it goes all the way to Darjeeling. The narrow rail track passes through the highest altitude railway station of Asia known as Ghoom. The journey is quite joyful as you can see the magnificent view of hills and valleys through the train\'s window.</p>\r\n<h2>NJP to Darjeeling by Bus</h2>\r\n<p>If you find it comfortable to travel by bus, this option is also available to go from NJP to Darjeeling. There are presently two bus services available and both of them are run by NBSTC. You even can take a bus from Siliguri. And in order to reach Siliguri from New Jalpaiguri, you can take any auto or Rickshaw. From Siliguri, you can get plenty of private buses and state buses to reach Darjeeling.</p>\r\n<h2>How to Return from Darjeeling</h2>\r\n<p>Finally, we have guided you to know all the details related to reaching Darjeeling from New Jalpaiguri. And now maybe you are thinking about the process of returning. Please don\'t worry because here at Himalayan Wheels we are here to help you out.</p>\r\n<p>During the time of returning, you can take the above-mentioned mediums to return. But if you need to return to your home quite comfortably after enjoying the beauty of Darjeeling, you can opt for our car rental service.</p>\r\n<h2>Why You Should Choose Us</h2>\r\n<p>There are plenty of reasons for which you can choose our car rental service. As we have already mentioned, the process of booking our car rental service is quite easy and hassle-free. All you have to do is just book our car and we will pick and drop you from your desired location. WE choose our employees and drivers who are well behaved. Our drivers are quite supportive too. And most importantly, if you have any complaints regarding our services, you are always welcome to contact us as you already know here at Himalayan Wheels, the customer is our first priority.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2019-07-16 10:04:46', '2019-07-13 13:11:16', NULL),
(29, 31, 8, '<h2>How to Travel from Bagdogra to Mirik</h2>\r\n<p>If your plan is to spend some days in Darjeeling, it would be great to enjoy some days in Mirik too. Mirik is a small beautiful town located in Darjeeling District of West Bengal. Mirik is a quite popular tourist hub because of its climate, easy accessibility, and natural environment. The weather of Mirik stays always charming. It never reaches to the point of extreme cold like Darjeeling&#39;s weather because Mirik has an average elevation of 1495m. The temperature of the city usually stays 30-degree Celsius during summer and a minimum of 1 degree Celsius during winter. So if you are planning to enjoy the beauty and charming weather of the city but don&#39;t know to travel from Bagdogra to Mirik, we are here to help you. But first, let&#39;s have a look at some of the attractive places in Mirik.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Mirik</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>BokarNgedonChokhor Ling Monastery is one of the attractive places in Sikkim. This beautiful monastery is the home of many Buddhists Monks and this monastery is a must-visit place if you want to see the culture and the lifestyle of these Buddhists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sumendu Lake is another attractive place to visit in Mirik. If your priority is tranquility and peace you can spend hours sitting beside this lake. Boating is quite fun here as you can enjoy the magnificent surroundings from the middle of the water. The magnificent dense forest around the lake gives an extra charm to the travelers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Roman Catholic Church is an eye-catching edifice in Mirik, standing next behind Don Bosco Scool. Due to its brilliant structural design and astounding surrounding, Don Bosco is quite popular among tourists and one of the best places to visit in Mirik.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need a mesmerizing view of lush tree gardens and a scenic view of snow-peaked mountains, Tingling Viewpoint is the ideal place for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Mirik by Road</h2>\r\n\r