(30, 31, 9, '<h2>How to Travel from Bagdogra to Phuentsholing</h2>\r\n<p>Traveling to an unknown place for the first time can be a little problematic and if you don&#39;t have proper guidance. If you have planned to travel from Bagdogra to Phuentsholing, here in this article let us guide you from first to last. Phuentsholing is the gateway of Bhutan and as you enter here you will witness the beauty of Bhutan with the clean surrounding. Surrounded by astounding hills, this place is quite ideal to escape from your crowded and bustling lifestyle and take rest in the lap of the mesmerizing beauty of Phuentsholing.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Phuentsholing</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In Phuentsholing, Buddism is not a religion but a way of life. Therefore, Phuentsholing has many Buddist&#39;s monasteries and Zangtho Pelri Lhakhang is one of them. If you want to experience the lifestyle Buddhists and want to get the blessing from Lord Buddha, this mesmerizing ancient monastery is a must-visit place for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Founded in 1967, Karbandi Monastery is another beautiful place to visit in Phuentsholing. The local name of this beautiful monastery is Karbandi Goemba, situated at a height of 400 meters. A beautiful garden is also there near the monastery from where you can get a panoramic view of the entire Phuentsholing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>AmoChhu Crocodile Breeding Farm is one of the main attractions of Phuensholing. If you were always curious to know about these deadly creatures but did not get a chance to see it closely, you can visit this crocodile breeding farm. You finally know some of the attractive places in Phuentsholing. Now let&#39;s talk about how to reach there.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Phuentsholing by Road</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Bus, shared taxis are not available from Bagdogra to Phuentsholing. If you want to save carfare, you can travel to Siliguri first. There are plenty of buses available which runs to Jaigaon and Phuentsholing. As you can see, the journey is full of