(31, 31, 5, '<h2>How to travel from Bagdogra to Jaigaon</h2>\r\n<p>If you are planning to visit Bhutan, the nearby city Jaigaon should be in your must-visit list. Jaigaon is a magnificent town of Alipurduar District in the state of West Bengal. It is a tiny town located near the low-lying hills of the Himalayan mountains. The city is surrounded by many scenic tea gardens and the Torsa River flows at the lower end of the town. The town is situated at the India-Bhutan border with Phuentsholing, therefore you will get a chance to travel to Bhutan to enjoy some Bhutanese places too. The town is quite small and you can easily see the city on foot. As of census 2011, the population of Jaigaon is just 42,254. Now, before diving into the question of how to reach there, let us showcase some of the attractive places in Jaigaon first.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Jaigaon</h2>\r\n<p>Jaigaon has plenty of reasons to attract travelers, as it is located near Bhutan, you can experience the mesmerizing beauty of this country. Bhutan Gate is nearby and you will get a chance to know and enjoy this eye-catching Bhutanese architecture. The temperature of the town is quite charming. The temperature stays at 22 degrees to 30 degrees during summer and 10 degrees to 24 degrees Celsius during winter. This town becomes a must-visit place if you want to escape the intense heat of summer.</p>\r\n<p>Karbandi Monastery is another attractive place to visit near Jaigaon. This Buddhist monastery is quite popular among tourists because of his ancient architecture and astounding view of surrounding places.</p>\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Jaigaon by Road</h2>\r\n<p>A hired car is available from Bagdogra to Jaigaon. After reaching Bagdogra get a taxi which is going to Jaigaon. Car drivers usually ask for high car fare while travelling from Bagdogra to Jaigaon.</p>\r\n<p>Buses are usually not available from Bagdogra to Jaigaon. But if you want to save some cost, you can go Siliguri first. From Siliguri plenty of