(33, 31, 7, '<h2>How to travel from Bagdogra to Lava</h2>\r\n<p>There are quite a few places in West Bengal where you can enjoy the snowfall and lava is one of them. This mesmerizing village is located 30 kilometers east of the Kalimpong town in the State of West Bengal. Blessed with rich flora and fauna, Lava is undoubtedly one of the most recommended tourist destinations in the West Bengal. The village is located at the altitude of 7100ft and as it is situated in the dense forest, it is too quiet and romantic. The journey from Bagdogra to Lava is too cheerful as this village is surrounded by many Alpine trees. Now before talking about how to travel from Bagdogra to Lava, know some of the attractive places in Lava first.</p>\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Lava</h2>\r\n<p>Lava can be tagged as a tourist\'s paradise as it is full of attractive and worth visiting places. You can completely fall in love with the village once you start exploring it. Lava\'s Kagyu Thekchen Ling Monastery is a beautiful Buddhist Monastery situated in the lap of Himalaya. Visit the monastery to get spiritually connected to Buddhism and feel the presence of Buddha everywhere. Changery Fall is situated at a distance of 10 km from this village and it is quite popular among tourists for its scenic beauty. Neora Valley National Park is another attractive place in Lava. If you want to enjoy the company of none other than nature, you must visit this wildlife-rich park. You can even see many animals here in Neora Valley National Park such as tigers, red panda, leopard and many more. Tiffin Dara View Point is another famous place of Lava for enjoying sunrise and sunset. Now if you are planning to travel from Bagdogra to Lava, you have come in the right place.</p>\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Lava by Road</h2>\r\n<p>Bus service is not available from Bagdogra to Lava. If you want to save some car fare, you can go up to Siliguri. From here, plenty of buses are available which go to Lava via Gorubathan and Kalimpong.