(34, 4, 32, '<h2>How to Travel from NJP to Gangtok</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Gangtok is the capital of Sikkim, a state situated in northeastern India. Gangtok is usually known as the Buddhist haven. There are many tourist places in Gangtok such as many Buddhist monasteries, Nathula Pass, Tsomgo Lake, etc. which make the city a must-visit destination for tourists. Situated near the eastern Himalayan range, the city is a combination of modern, resort town style with ancient spiritual beliefs and impressive natural heritage. If you are planning to experience the calmness and beauty of this scenic cityto get relief from your hectic lifestyle but know nothing about the transportation system, we are here to help you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your plan is to travel from NJP to Gangtok, there are plenty of options available. Here we are going to discuss about all the transportation systems to reach Gangtok, their advantages, and even their disadvantages and why you should always choose our car rental service.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Njp to Gangtok by Taxi</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The most convenient way to go to Gangtok is by road because the access to railway route is limited in Sikkim. After reaching NJP station, you can opt for a taxi or a taxi rental service like Himalayan Wheels. The drivers usually ask more than the fair price and which can be quite uncomfortable and costly for you. But here at Himalayan Wheels, we always ask for the exact price and the cars we provide are also quite comfortable. The drivers we provide are experienced enough and know how to behave politely with customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>NJP to Gangtok by Shared Taxi</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If your plan is to go for a little cheap option, you can take a shared taxi. You can find many shared taxis from NJP railway station or even from Siliguri. You have to bear troubles if you want to get a shared taxi from Siliguri as you must take an auto to reach there. Shared taxis usually does not start until it is completely full, thus you have to wait and let