(35, 31, 12, '<h2>How to travel from Bagdogra to Lolegaon</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are seeking for peace and want to enjoy the breathtaking beauty of nature, you should at least travel once to Lolegaon. It is a fascinating Lepcha hamlet with a population of just 5000 people. At an altitude of 1675 meters, it is situated at the extreme end of the Himalayan ridge in the Kalimpong District of West Bengal. It is undoubtedly naturs&#39;s paradise. Known for its simplicity and the panoramic view of Mount Kanchenjunga, there are also many attractive places located in Lolegaon. Let&#39;s dive into all of them one by one and later get to know about all the mediums needed to reach there.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Places to Visit in Lolegaon&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Lolegaon is full of attractive places and Neora Valley Nation Park is one of them. If you are a nature and birds lover, this park becomes a must-visit travel destination for you. Feel the solace of nature and get to know some interesting facts about a cute creature named Red Panda. The park is also a home of various other wild animals and trees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get closer to a Buddhist Monastery and feel the presence of Lord Buddha everywhere at Lava Jamgyong Kongtrul Monastery. Know this oldest Tibetan architecture and get an astonishing panoramic view of the entire village as well as of the mountains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Experience walking on a 180 meters long wooden tree-top bridge. It is hanging from one tree to another. View the beauty of the forest from a reasonable height and feel the continuous swing of the bridge. Get the majestic view of Kanchenjunga and Mount Everest from a wooden hilltop named Jhandi Dara. Get a chance to experience the most cherished memory of your life by seeing the sunrise over the snow-peaked Kanchenjungha.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Lolegaon by Road</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Bus service is not directly available from Bagdogra to Lolegaon. If you want to save some car fare, you can go up to Siliguri. From Siliguri&#39;s P.C Mittal Bus Stand, plenty of buses available that go to Lolegaon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Shared taxis are also not available from Bagdogra to Lolegao. For a shared taxi, you again have to go to Siliguri. So if you wanted to save some car fare, it is not going to happen. In this situation, a hired taxi is the best choice for you but the drivers try to charge more car fare from Bagdogra to Lava. Therefore, you have to keep bargaining with them to get the cheap price.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That is why we suggest Himalayan Wheels car rental service to travel from Bagdogra to Lolegaon. Here you don&#39;t have to bargain, don&#39;t have to change any vehicles, just contact, choose your desired car and you are done.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Lolegaon by Train</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There is no railway station in Lolegaon. The nearest station of the village is New Jalpaiguri which is well connected with various major railway stations of the country. But the lack of the railway station in the village makes it impossible for a tourist to travel Lolegaon by train. The only option to travel from NJP to Lolegaon is by road and this is why we are offering our cheap and convenient car rental service to you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Bagdogra to Lolegaon by Air</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Lolegaon does not have an airport. The nearest one is Bagdogra Airport which is 100 km away from the Village. Bagdogra is well connected with various airports nationally and even internationally. As we can see travelling from NJP to Lolegaon by air is impossible as this village has no airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to Return from Lolegaon</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You don&#39;t have to think much about the process of returning. Himalayan wheels also offer a car rental service to return from Lolegaon. We ensure you that the journey while returning will also be quite comfortable. So, the next time you visit Lolegaon, don&#39;t forget to opt for Himalayan Wheels car rental service for your both journey.</p>\r\n', 'dsfd', NULL, NULL, 13